detailedRequirements:
2nd place prize : We will keep challenge active for 24hrs after accepting first submission, anyone submit a valid submission before end of the 24hrs period will get a $400.

Task Overview

The goal of this challenge is to build a proof of concept for converting an image to xml using Image processing and OCR technology.

Task Requirements

You are provided with a PDF input that includes two images, and you will need to build a tool that accurately extract content of the sections we want to parse. You are recommended to do a research for an open source PDF processing, Image processing and OCR library that can be used in java, for OCR library it seems tesseract ocr is sufficient for what we are trying to accompilsh in this challenge.

In the provided input image we have two main content that we want to ranslate into xml :

  • Application Number : as in the screenshot
  • Tables content : In sample input we have two tables :
    • the first one we call it table because it has borders but the content does not represents a single table you can see we have three main sections in the table of first page :
      • The "Documents considered to be relevant table"
        • Note that rows does not have separators, the first and third columns row separator is space, while the 2nd row separator is ----- which you can assume this separator always the same.
        • The 2nd column cell value is multi-lines, the line start with * and ends with * character except the first line.
        • The table headers are always the same in all input documents.
      • Classification of the application section
        • The column header is part of the document template, always the same
      • Technical Fields Searched
        • The column header is part of the document template, always the same
      • Search report metadata
        • The headers are part of the document template, always the same
      • Category of Cited Documents (this section is always the same as it is part of the template, used by explain what category column values mean)
  • The second table is much easier to parse, it is a standard table with multiple columns, where row separators are ---- and some row fields are multilines.
    • The column headers are part of the document template, they are always the same.

We need you to build a command line utility that performs the following :

  • Accepts the image file and location of output file as input arguments
  • We are not looking for a generic implementation for parsing and extracing content from PDF, the provided PDF is a template, the row values in the tables and application number are variables and they are the only content in scope
  • Process the PDF file as follow :
    • Split the PDF into multiple pages (You can use PDF open source library, most of them support it)
    • Convert each page to image, convert it to black and while, and increase it's resolution to improve next steps of image processing (you can also find open source libraries that support this conversion)
    • For each image, locate the horizontal and vertical lines of each table
    • Segment the tables into cells using line coordinates
      • You also need to segment the header above table to extract application number. A solution would be to locate the top line of the table of first page, and slice the image from that part and OCR it, it should give you Application Number text and the value right after it in the next line in the returned text.
    • Cleanup cells, remove borders ..etc
    • Peform OCR on each cell (including header of first image)
    • Assemble results into key/value dictionary
  • Build the XML from returned dictionary
  • Store the xml in passed in dictory, if not present then store it in default preconfigured location
  • Return full path and exit the tool

Documents

Provided in challenge forums the XSD file, and 3 samples of input files and their output.

Test

We will use the samples to test your solution, the output is expected to match the provided output samples. Make sure to test them thoroughly.

Deliverable

  • A Fully implemented solution that addresses the requirements above.
  • A detailed readme to setup and run the tool.
